seed7-mode -- Seed7 Classic Emacs Mode -- NEWS     -*- org -*-


* New in seed7-mode since 2026-05-01

** New Commands

- *seed7-run-program*: Run a Seed7 program directly from Emacs.  The
  command first performs a static check; if no error is found it
  launches the program via the configured interpreter and displays its
  standard output and standard error in two separate windows named
  =*seed7-run: BASENAME*= and =*seed7-run-stderr: BASENAME*=.
  The run buffer supports two input modes:
  - *Buffered mode* (default): input is sent to the program when =RET=
    is pressed; all normal Emacs key bindings remain active.
    - Switch to raw mode by typing ~C-c C-k~.
  - *Raw mode*: every key stroke (except ~C-c C-j~ and ~C-c C-c~) is
    sent directly to the program.
    - Switch to buffered mode by typing ~C-c C-j~.

- *seed7-rebuild-abbrev-table*: Reload the abbreviation table after
  customizing the user-options that control it.  The command checks for
  duplicates and errors, and warns the user of any issue found.

** Renamed Commands

- *seed7-compile* was renamed to *seed7-check-or-compile*, which
  better reflects that the command performs either a static check or a
  full compilation depending on the checker/compiler configured.  The
  key binding is unchanged.

- *seed7-line-inside-proc-argument-list-section* was renamed to
  *seed7-line-inside-argument-list-section* and its logic fixed.

** New Internal Helpers

- *seed7--cmd-specs-for*: Centralizes executable path resolution and
  command-line construction for all Seed7 tool invocations.

- *seed7--end-msg-for*: Centralizes the formatting of execution-result
  messages (diagnostics count, pluralization, stderr inclusion,
  exit-code reporting) used by *seed7-check-or-compile* and
  *seed7-run-program*.

- *seed7--run* and *seed7--parse-diagnostics*: Low-level helpers that
  execute an external tool and parse its diagnostic output,
  respectively.

- *seed7--with-forward-sexp* and *seed7--with-backward-sexp*: Macros
  that protect call sites against =scan-error= signals from
  *forward-sexp* and *backward-sexp*.  They can be compiled with
  additional logging/debugging code.

** Improvements

- Regular expressions used to detect keywords and used in navigation now
  allow hard tabs as whitespace following keywords.
  Hard tabs are not encouraged; Seed7 recommends spaces.  They are tolerated
  in existing indentation and after a single keyword, but not between the two
  words of a dual keyword (e.g. "end func").

- *forward-sexp for comments, blocks, procedures and functions*:
  *forward-sexp* and *backward-sexp* can now move across:
  - Seed7 =(*= ... =*)= nested block comments,
  - single and consecutive =#= line-end comments,
  - nested statement blocks,
  - function and procedure blocks.

- *Syntax propertization*: *seed7-mode-syntax-propertize* is now
  wrapped in *with-silent-modifications*, making it safe whether called
  by =jit-lock= or directly.

- *Comment detection*: *seed7-inside-comment-p* now uses syntax-table
  information instead of font-lock face properties, eliminating a race
  condition where a check performed before font-locking completed could
  yield incorrect results.

- *Nested block comment support*: The =(*= ... =*)= comment
  rendering now correctly handles nested block comments.

- *Indentation speed*: Multiple improvements to *seed7-calc-indent*
  and related helpers which significantly improves speed in large files:
  - Block boundary positions are cached per indentation pass,
    dramatically reducing repeated searches in large files.
  - *indent-step* is now computed lazily inside *seed7-calc-indent*.
  - Functions that return early on lines not meeting their preconditions
    have been made faster by checking the simplest condition first.
  - *seed7--indent-offset-for* now receives the pre-extracted line text
    from *seed7-line-inside-a-block*, avoiding redundant buffer scans.
  - *seed7-line-inside-a-block-cached* added to reduce repeated calls
    from *seed7-indent-line* on multi-line statements.

- *Xref support*:
  - Cache is now invalidated when the Seed7 buffer is saved or reverted.
  - *seed7-xref* =~= expansion, space-in-path handling, and failing
    exit-code reporting improved.
  - *seed7--build-xref* now refuses to operate on a buffer not visiting
    a file, and warns when the buffer has unsaved changes.

- *Error handling for static check / compilation*:
  - *seed7-check-or-compile* now shows the program name, exit code,
    stderr text, and parsed diagnostics in the result buffer and echo
    area.
  - *seed7-check-file* correctly distinguishes =s7c= (diagnostics on
    stderr) from =s7check= (diagnostics on stdout).
  - Buffer leaks on exception during tool invocation are now prevented.

- *Emacs compatibility*: *string-split* replaced by *split-string* and
  *when-let* replaced by its expansion so that seed7-mode continues to
  work on Emacs 25.1 and later.

- *Compiler optimization declarations*: Side-effect-free and pure
  function declarations added to help the byte and native compilers
  produce better code.

- *seed7-re-search-forward-closest* and
  *seed7-re-search-backward-closest* improved: both now guarantee that
  the global match data on return corresponds to the regexp search that
  found the closest element.

- =s7xref= tool: command-line help (=--help=) and argument validation
  added.

** Bug Fixes

- Fix *excessive indentation of sibling catch statements*.  Issue reported by /barankegnu/
  in [[https://github.com/pierre-rouleau/seed7-mode/issues/79][bug-79]].

- Fix *seed7-line-inside-parens-pair*: was using the wrong variable for
  the line-beginning position.

- Fix *seed7-symbol-at-point*: was using *looking-at-p* (does not
  update match data) instead of *looking-at* in one branch.

- Fix *seed7-re-search-backward-closest*: no longer returns match data
  from the last-searched regexp instead of the winning regexp.

- Fix *nth* calls that were incorrectly using 1-based indexing.

- Fix *seed7-nav-beginning-of-defun*: *nil* argument is now treated as
  *1*, consistent with *forward-defun* conventions.

- Fix *seed7--xref-get-from-s7xref*: was using the file name of the
  internal xref result buffer instead of the source buffer's file name.

- Fix *seed7-inside-comment-p* and
  *seed7-current-line-start-inside-comment-p* to work correctly after
  the switch from font-lock to syntax-table–based comment detection.

- Fix comment rendering regression after introducing syntax-table
  text-property–based block comment support.

- Fix Emacs 29.4 byte-compilation regression (bug `#1058739`) in the
  diagnostic parsing code.

- Fix *seed7-check-file* path expansion for the checked file.

- Fix various regexp typos in token-matching patterns.

- Fix *seed7-indentation-of-previous-non-string-line*: now returns
  *nil* (instead of a meaningless integer) when no non-string line is
  found.

- Prevent possible out-of-bounds buffer positions (*1+*, *1-*) inside
  *seed7-calc-indent* when operating at buffer edges.

** Build / CI

- GitHub Actions workflows added for multi-platform byte and native
  compilation:
  - Linux (Docker/silex image)
  - Linux (apt-get + Homebrew based)
  - Windows (manual and push triggered)
  - macOS (Homebrew)
  - Emacs versions: 25.1 and later
  Workflows succeed only when there are zero errors and zero compiler
  warnings.

- Timing measurement tool *seed7-mode-time.el* added under =tools/= to
  help measure the execution time of individual commands.
